OL,3,CBristol Airport 'scathing' over Welsh
OL,4,CGovernment's subsidy for Cardiff
OL,5,CAirport
OL,7,FWriting to Welsh Government Minister
OL,8,FRebecca Evans MS, Bristol Airport said
OL,9,Fthe proposed subsidy would exceed
OL,10,FCardiff Airport's current annual
OL,11,Fturnover, in each year of the planned
OL,12,F10-year duration and comes on top of
OL,13,Fthe nearly #200m of taxpayers' money
OL,14,Falready provided to Cardiff Airport.
OL,16,FBristol Airport claim the funding has
OL,17,Fpotential to "distort competition, and
OL,18,Frisks reducing air travel choice for
OL,19,Fcustomers, including those living in
OL,20,FSouth Wales".
